the psychology of hostage-takers.

101
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,880
It's either in uncontrollable rage

102
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,380
or scornful of everything.

103
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:03,880
So we need to use humanitarianism
to change their mindset.

104
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,520
Very well.

105
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,920
But it's all just theory.

106
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,520
We need to adjust
based on the actual situation.

107
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,120
Yuan Bin was a juvenile offender.

108
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:20,480
After rehabilitation, he worked hard

109
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,280
and became an accountant.

110
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,160
He was fired
because of his past blemish,

111
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,000
so he must hate those

112
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,960
who deny his efforts.

113
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,600
So

114
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,440
we need to shift Yuan Bin's attention

115
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:35,680
away from Manager Zhou.

116
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,480
Pretty good.

117
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,120
Remember,

118
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,280
during the negotiation process,

119
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,200
we must always be aware
of the suspect's state of mind.

120
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,120
Once our words

121
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,680
don't resonate with him,

122
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,760
the suspect will easily

123
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:57,680
lose patience

124
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,700
and cease communication.

125
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,720
This could lead to mission failure.

126
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,600
By the way,

127
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:07,160
the donations for Yuan Bin's mother

128
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,600
have all been given to the hospital.

129
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,440
And I heard the donations
are still coming in.

130
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:13,320
Great.

131
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,040
Captain, goodbye.

132
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,680
Yuan Bin,

133
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,440
I'm here to tell you

134
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,520
Manager Zhou has signed
a letter of understanding

135
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,280
and has been writing to the court.

136
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,840
They are still working for your case.

137
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,120
Here's some good news.

138
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,480
The hospital has received donations
from all sectors of society.

139
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:54,080
Your mother's medical fees
are no longer an issue.

140
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,360
Don't worry.

141
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,760
This is a recent video of your mom.

142
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,600
Drink slowly. Don't choke.

143
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,240
Her health is stable.

144
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,240
Thank you.

145
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,920
It's no problem.

146
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,200
I'll peel an orange for you.

147
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,040
Where's Bin?

148
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,960
Bin?

149
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,760
He went on a business trip.

150
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:19,080
He told me to come
and help take care of you.

151
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,880
Bin is really impressive now.

152
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,600
Our boss at the head office

153
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,680
saw him once.

154
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,320
He said

155
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,760
that Bin is very hardworking,

156
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,540
and they are preparing to send him
for training at the head office.

157
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,080
Thanks for their care.

158
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:35,640
It's no problem.

159
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,240
It's because Bin did well.

160
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,520
Get more Vitamin C.

161
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,040
It's good for your health, right?

162
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:41,560
And your medical fees

163
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,040
have been taken concern.

164
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:43,880
No worries now.

165
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:44,900
You don't need to worry.

166
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,460
Right.

167
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,280
Thanks for your help.

168
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:50,120
It's the least we could do.

169
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,480
Here, have another one.

170
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,000
Okay, thank you.

171
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:13,920
Sorry.

172
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,680
I'm leaving.

173
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,880
Pass.

174
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,440
Quick, quick, quick.

175
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,200
What happened?

176
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,520
What place is this?

177
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,560
Hello, where's my bestie outfit?

178
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,880
It's ready.

179
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,520
Here.

180
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,040
Tata.

181
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,400
How about this dress?

182
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,040
It looks pretty good.

183
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,400
It suits you.

184
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,480
Too bad it's a bestie outfit.

185
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:34,800
Fang Fang isn't here.

186
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:37,440
